Harmony Gold Rises After Saying Profit to Benefit From $50 Million Credit

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-04-13T10:56:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/harmony-gold-rises-after-saying-profit-to-benefit-from-50-million-credit.html
Harmony Gold Mining Ltd. rose in
Johannesburg trading after saying earnings per share excluding
one-time items will be boosted by a tax credit of about 330
million rand.  The stock rose 1.54 rand, or 1.6 percent, to 101.04 rand as
of 12:55 p.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Carli Lourens at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net  